{"artifact_links": ["https://simonwillison.net/2026/May/3/anthropic"], "author_or_org": null, "canonical_url": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/May/3/anthropic", "collection_method": "rss_atom", "confidence": "high", "content_hash": "2322f888cbdc11ef", "dedup_key": "rss-guid:simonwillison-blog:https://simonwillison.net/2026/May/3/anthropic/#atom-everything", "event_id": "event_33552b67ed914743", "evidence_type": "supported_fact", "excerpt": "<blockquote cite=\"https://www.anthropic.com/research/claude-personal-guidance\"><p>We used an automatic classifier which judged sycophancy by looking at whether Claude showed a willingness to push back, maintain positions when challenged, give praise proportional to the merit of ideas, and speak frankly regardless of what a person wants to hear. Most of the time in these situations, Claude expressed no sycophancy\u2014only 9% of conversations included sycophantic behavior (Figure 2). But two domains were exceptions: we saw sycophantic behavior in 38% of conversations focused on spirituality, and 25% of conversations on relationships.</p></blockquote>\n<p class=\"cite\">&mdash; <a href=\"https://www.anthropic.com/research/claude-personal-guidance\">Anthropic</a>, How people ask Claude for personal guidance</p>\n\n    <p>Tags: <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/ai-ethics\">ai-ethics</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/anthropic\">anthropic</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/claude\">claude</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/ai-personality\">ai-personality</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/generative-ai\">generative-ai</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net", "identifiers": {}, "inferred_entities": [], "item_type": "rss_atom_item", "novelty_score": 0.0, "published_at": "2026-05-03T15:13:23+00:00", "ranking_explanation": "", "raw_metadata": {}, "relevance_score": 0.0, "retrieved_at": "2026-05-03T22:16:58Z", "source_id": "simonwillison-blog", "source_name": "Simon Willison's Weblog", "source_native_id": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/May/3/anthropic/#atom-everything", "source_policy": "public_official", "source_type": "primary_artifact", "summary_hint": "<blockquote cite=\"https://www.anthropic.com/research/claude-personal-guidance\"><p>We used an automatic classifier which judged sycophancy by looking at whether Claude showed a willingness to push back, maintain positions when challenged, give praise proportional to the merit of ideas, and speak frankly regardless of what a person wants to hear. Most of the time in these situations, Claude expressed no sycophancy\u2014only 9% of conversations included sycophantic behavior (Figure 2). But two domains were exceptions: we saw sycophantic behavior in 38% of conversations focused on spirituality, and 25% of conversations on relationships.</p></blockquote>\n<p class=\"cite\">&mdash; <a href=\"https://www.anthropic.com/research/claude-personal-guidance\">Anthropic</a>, How people ask Claude for personal guidance</p>\n\n    <p>Tags: <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/ai-ethics\">ai-ethics</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/anthropic\">anthropic</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/claude\">claude</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/ai-personality\">ai-personality</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/generative-ai\">generative-ai</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net", "title": "Quoting Anthropic", "topics": ["topic_quoting-anthropic"], "updated_at": null}
